'''IndiaMART InterMESH Ltd''' is an Indian [[B2B e-commerce|B2B]] [[online marketplace]], connecting buyers and suppliers. It is headquartered in [[Noida]]. The company started its operations in 1996 when [[Dinesh Agarwal]] and Brijesh Agrawal founded the website IndiaMART.com,<ref name="Disha Sharma">{{cite web | url=http://www.vccircle.com/news/telecom/2016/01/04/exclusive-indiamarts-agarwal-backs-office-products-portal-instaproc | title=Indiamart's Agarwal backs office products portal ProcMart | publisher=[[VCCircle]] | date=4 January 2016 | access-date=27 January 2016 | author=Disha Sharma | archive-date=25 October 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025011409/http://www.vccircle.com/news/telecom/2016/01/04/exclusive-indiamarts-agarwal-backs-office-products-portal-instaproc | url-status=dead }}</ref> a [[business-to-business]] portal to connect Indian manufacturers with buyers.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://retail.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/e-commerce/e-tailing/indiamart-eyes-rs-2000-cr-revenue-by-2020/48986352 | title=Indiamart eyes Rs 2,000 cr revenue by 2020 | work=[[Indiatimes.com]] | date=16 September 2015 | access-date=27 January 2016 | author=Varun Jain}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/management/indiamart-small-business-means-big-business-115081600627_1.html | title=IndiaMART: Small business means big business | work=[[Business Standard]] | date=17 August 2015 | access-date=27 January 2016 | author=Ankita Rai}}</ref>

==History==
Founded in 1996 by two cousins [[Dinesh Agarwal]] and Brijesh Agrawal, IndiaMART began as a B2B directory and website developer for SMEs.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://bwdisrupt.businessworld.in/article/IndiaMART-To-Stream-50-of-Revenue-from-Big-Brands-by-2020-/21-02-2017-113217/| title= IndiaMART To Stream 50% of Revenue from Big Brands by 2020| publisher= Business World| date=21 February 2017 | access-date=13 October 2019| author= Soumya Gupta }}</ref> At that time, India had only 15,000 internet users.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/companies/dot-com-bust-was-the-best-thing-that-happened-to-us/articleshow/70322708.cms| title= 'Dot-com bust was the best thing that happened to us'| publisher= Times Of India| date=22 July 2019 | access-date=12 October 2019| author= Dijbijay Mishra}}</ref> 

Due to [[Indian rupee]]'s appreciation between 2005 and 2007 and the impact of the 2008–09 [[Great Recession|US recession]], the company decided to pivot the focus from export-oriented business to India-focused B2B market and raised funding from [[The Times Group]] and [[Intel Capital]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/IndiaMart-com-gets-funds-from-Intel-Capital/articleshow/3979827.cms | title=IndiaMart.com gets funds from Intel Capital | newspaper=[[Times of India]] | date=14 January 2009 | access-date=27 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/rs-1-crore-a-day-is-not-far-away-for-pe-backed-indiamart-115071600014_1.html | title=Rs 1 crore a day is not far away for PE-backed Indiamart | newspaper=[[Business Standard]] | date=16 July 2015 | access-date=27 January 2016 | author=N Sundaresha Subramanian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Chatterjee |first1=Paramita |last2=Nair |first2=Radhika P. |title=Warburg Pincus in t
